    <section id="practice">
      <h2>What To Do in Practice</h2>

      <p>The research points to a sequence that works for most B2B teams and affiliate marketers building lead-dependent businesses.</p>

      <ol>
        <li><strong>Start with ICP definition, not with channel selection.</strong> Write down specifically which job titles, company sizes, and industries describe your ideal buyers. Every channel and content decision follows from this.</li>
        <li><strong>Pick two or three channels before expanding to six.</strong> The lowest-resistance starting stack: SEO-driven content (lowest CPL, highest close rate), email nurture (lowest cost to maintain contact over a 10-month B2B cycle), and LinkedIn (direct outreach and thought leadership).</li>
        <li><strong>Build the nurture sequence before worrying about top-of-funnel volume.</strong> A contact captured without a follow-up plan loses most of its value within a week. Even a four-email sequence sent over 30 days outperforms no sequence by a significant margin.</li>
        <li><strong>Measure cost per lead by channel.</strong> Compare your numbers against the benchmarks above. If your SEO CPL is $120 but the benchmark is $31, the gap is fixable once you can see it.</li>
        <li><strong>Set up an alert for high-intent signals and follow up within 5 minutes.</strong> The 9x conversion advantage of a 5-minute response is one of the highest-ROI optimizations available and requires no additional spend.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

